TITLE: New Orleans Jazz Fest cancels 2021 event due to Covid-19
SUMMARY: Rising cases of Covid-19 in Louisiana have led to the cancellation of the New Orleans Jazz Fest for the second year running, organizers announced Sunday.

TITLE: Executive assistant to Andrew Cuomo details allegations of sexual harassment by New York governor
SUMMARY: An assistant to New York Gov. Andrew Cuomo, who until now has only been referred to as "Executive Assistant 1," has publicly identified herself and detailed her claims of sexual harassment by the embattled Democratic governor.

TITLE: A Chicago police officer is dead and another is fighting for his life following a shooting during a traffic stop
SUMMARY: One Chicago police officer is dead and another is fighting for his life after they were shot while conducting a traffic stop Saturday night, officials said.

TITLE: California's Dixie Fire now second-largest in state's history
SUMMARY: The Dixie Fire in California, the largest wildfire currently burning in the country, has grown to become the second-biggest in the state's history, according to CalFire.

TITLE: One killed, six injured in shooting at a Houston nightclub
SUMMARY: One person died and six others were injured in a shooting early Sunday morning at an after-hours bar in Houston, according to a statement on social media from Harris County Sheriff Ed Gonzalez.

TITLE: NBA Wizards-Pacers Summer League game postponed due to Covid-19 health and safety protocols
SUMMARY: The NBA Summer League game between the Washington Wizards and Indiana Pacers has been postponed due to the league's health and safety protocols.

TITLE: Julie Bowen of 'Modern Family' helped rescue a hiker who fainted in a Utah national park
SUMMARY: Actor Julie Bowen of "Modern Family" and her sister helped rescue a hiker when she fainted last week at Arches National Park in Moab, Utah, the hiker told CNN.

TITLE: Paul Whelan released from solitary confinement in Russian prison
SUMMARY: Paul Whelan, a US citizen detained in Russia, has been released from solitary confinement and was able to speak with his parents, his brother David Whelan told CNN Sunday.

TITLE: 6 members of a Florida church died of Covid-19 in 2 weeks, pastor says. On Sunday the church held a vaccination clinic
SUMMARY: In just two weeks, six members of a Florida church died from Covid-19. All were unvaccinated, their pastor said.

TITLE: Parents and students caught in political skirmishes over mask and vaccine mandates
SUMMARY: The back-to-school season is turning into a frightening one for parents and children as they find themselves in the middle of political skirmishes over mask and vaccine mandates, leaving students' safety determined more by geography and the political whims of governors than the science that should be guiding best practices.

TITLE: Women athletes powered Team USA's Olympic victory
SUMMARY: Amy Bass reflects on the various ways that the Tokyo Olympics pushed boundaries -- in gender roles, in pandemic protocols, and more. Despite the increased pressure and dangers presented by the pandemic, Japan rose to the challenge to protect athletes from around the world.

TITLE: These 5 figures show how bad the US Covid-19 surge is. But experts say we can turn things around
SUMMARY: As the rate of Covid-19 vaccinations climbed and new infection numbers plummeted in spring, many Americans thought they were in for a carefree summer. But lagging vaccinations and a highly contagious new variant dragged the US back into a vicious Covid-19 surge -- one that's prompted new mask mandates and measures and still shows no signs of slowing down.

TITLE: As Canada reopens to Americans, emotions and hope run high on both sides of the border
SUMMARY: US tourists will be allowed back into Canada at 12:01 a.m. ET Monday. On both sides of the border, this long-awaited move is being met with anticipation and emotion.

TITLE: 'All the beds are taken up by Covid victims': Hospitals in the South are running out of space or staff
SUMMARY: Covid-19 hospitalizations are reaching all-time highs in parts of the South, with some patients unable to get the care they would normally receive.

TITLE: 2 dead, 3 wounded after man opens fire at New York City party
SUMMARY: Two people were killed and three others wounded when a gunman opened fire at a party in New York City early Sunday, police said.

TITLE: 5 injured in New Orleans shooting on Bourbon Street
SUMMARY: The victims were taken to the hospital with non-life-threatening injuries, at least three of victims suffered graze wounds, police said.

TITLE: Prolonged period of 'potentially dangerous heat' becoming more likely for the Northwest, weather service warns
SUMMARY: More than 260 million people in the United States are forecast to experience highs of at least 90 degrees by the end of this week as a new heat wave envelops the Northwest, threatening the region with record-breaking, dangerous temperatures.

TITLE: Biden praises US Olympians while Trump is only vocal when they lose
SUMMARY: Dean Obeidallah writes about the contrast between President Joe Biden's treatment of Olympians -- categorically celebrating their victories -- with former President Donald Trump, who's approval depends on whether the winner aligns with him politically.

TITLE: 'Good Morning America' weekend anchor Dan Harris is leaving after 21 years
SUMMARY: "Good Morning America" weekend anchor Dan Harris is leaving ABC News.

TITLE: Taliban seizes Kunduz, first major Afghan city to fall in vacuum left by US troop withdrawal
SUMMARY: The Taliban has seized control of Kunduz in northern Afghanistan, local officials told CNN on Sunday. It is the first major city to fall to the insurgent group since they began their offensive in May, and marks a big blow to the Afghan government.

TITLE: Race against time: Inside ATF's efforts to find shooters before they strike again
SUMMARY: DC's police force and special agents from the Bureau of Alcohol, Tobacco, Firearms and Explosives (ATF) have joined forces to surge resources towards stopping the next shooting. It is one of five ATF efforts underway across the nation in cities experiencing significant gun violence.

TITLE: Starting this month, you can shop at Sephora in some Kohl's stores
SUMMARY: Kohl's and Sephora are teaming up to go beyond the shopping mall and bring more makeup to customers.

TITLE: Chinese regulators eye unruly online fans and pop culture shows as their next crackdown targets
SUMMARY: Chinese internet and media regulators are pledging to come down hard on "unhealthy" online fan groups as supporters of pop star Kris Wu took to social media to vehemently defend him against allegations of rape.

TITLE: At least 2 killed, 11 wounded in three overnight shootings in Chicago
SUMMARY: Three shootings in Chicago overnight killed two people, including a Chicago police officer, and left at least 11 others wounded, according to Chicago police.

TITLE: Actress Markie Post dies at 70 after battle with cancer
SUMMARY: Markie Post, the actress known for her roles in "Night Court" and "The Fall Guy," has died. She was 70 years old.

TITLE: Big Tech has its eyes set on the metaverse. Here's what that means
SUMMARY: Facebook has many pressing problems, from proposed antitrust legislation to accusations that the company is contributing to vaccine misinformation. But when CEO Mark Zuckerberg joined a recent conference call with analysts to discuss its latest quarterly results, much of the focus was on something far removed from those issues: the metaverse. During the hour-long call, the metaverse was mentioned nearly two dozen times.

TITLE: Trevor Moore, comedian and co-founder of The Whitest Kids U Know, dead at 41
SUMMARY: Trevor Moore, comedian, actor, producer, and co-founder of the sketch comedy group The Whitest Kids U Know, has died at the age of 41.

TITLE: Physicians want the media to change the way Covid is being covered
SUMMARY: Media coverage of Covid-19 is constantly shifting and adapting as the Delta variant continues to spread around the globe â€” and physicians are getting frustrated.

TITLE: What some progressive activists fail to realize: Democrats like their party
SUMMARY: But while that win and those that came in other 2021 elections can be seen as moderates beating progressives, what it really shows is how Democratic voters actually like their party and its leadership.

TITLE: Education secretary pleads with politicians making it harder to control Covid-19 pandemic
SUMMARY: Education Secretary Miguel Cardona issued a plea on Sunday to politicians making it harder to control the pandemic while two Republicans called for local officials to make decisions regarding masks in schools amid the fallout over state bans on masks as Covid-19 cases continue to rise.
